1	//axhob_operation
2	{rbtgo_director_divest}
3	
4	NOTE: This operation divests a
5	{rbtr_director}
6	{giam_service_account}
7	from the
8	{rbtgi_depot_project}.
9	The
10	{rbtr_governor}
11	reads the role's installed RBRA, extracts the SA email from the `client_email` field, issues a REST DELETE against the IAM API, and removes the production RBRA file from disk to mirror cloud state and prevent stale-credential reuse.
12	No arguments required; the target SA is derived entirely from the kindled regime and the role's installed credential file.
13	
14	//axhos_step
15	. *Authenticate as
16	{rbtr_governor}*:
17	.. Execute
18	{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
19	.. {rbbc_store}
20	`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
21	
22	//axhos_step
23	. *Read Role RBRA and Extract Service Account Email*:
24	.. {rbbc_require}
25	the role's installed RBRA file exists at
26	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
27	.. {rbbc_fatal}
28	if the file is missing: "Director RBRA file not found — director may not have been invested"
29	.. {rbbc_store}
30	`«SA_EMAIL»` from the `client_email` field of
31	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
32	.. {rbbc_fatal}
33	if `client_email` is empty or absent: "Director RBRA file present but client_email field is missing or empty"
34	
35	//axhos_step
36	. *Divest Director Service Account*:
37	.. {rbbc_call}
38	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.delete] with:
39	... method: `DELETE`
40	... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts/«SA_EMAIL»`
41	... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
42	.. {rbbc_require}
43	HTTP 200 response OR HTTP 404 (already divested)
44	.. {rbbc_warn}
45	if HTTP 404: "Service account not found (already divested)"
46	
47	//axhos_step
48	. *Confirm Deletion Propagated*:
49	.. {rbbc_poll}
50	the SA GET endpoint until HTTP 404 confirms the
51	{giam_service_account}
52	is gone — a delete-accepted response precedes propagation, so an immediately following same-name
53	{rbtgo_director_invest}
54	would otherwise race a still-visible account
55	.. NOTE: skipped when the DELETE returned HTTP 404 — the account was already absent, so there is nothing to wait for
56	.. {rbbc_require}
57	HTTP 404 within the eventual-consistency deadline
58	
59	//axhos_step
60	. *Remove Production RBRA File*:
61	.. Remove the role's RBRA file at
62	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
63	from disk
64	.. {rbbc_require}
65	file removal successful or file already absent
66	.. NOTE: Removing the RBRA file mirrors cloud state locally and prevents any process from reusing a credential that no longer corresponds to an active
67	{giam_service_account}.
68	
69	//axhos_step
70	. *Display Result*:
71	.. {rbbc_show}
72	single-line success naming `«SA_EMAIL»` and confirming the
73	{rbtr_director}
74	{giam_service_account}
75	was divested, or a notice that it was already absent
76	
77	//axhoc_completion
78	Successful execution removes the
79	{rbtr_director}
80	{giam_service_account}
81	from
82	{rbtgi_depot_project}
83	and deletes the local RBRA credential file.
84	Cloud state and local credential state are left in agreement: no stale key file remains after a successful divest.
85	A 404 response from the cloud DELETE is accepted as success — the
86	{giam_service_account}
87	is absent either way, and the RBRA file is removed regardless.
88	Proceed to
89	{rbtgo_director_invest}
90	to re-issue a fresh
91	{rbtr_director}
92	{giam_service_account}
93	when needed.
94

